  "prompt": "What etnicity would you describe me as? I am originally Iranian, this is due to most questions of \"ethnicity \" options on each application form?",
  "response": "When you encounter questions about ethnicity on application forms, it\u2019s important to understand that ethnicity refers to shared cultural, national, or ancestral identity, rather than nationality or citizenship. Since you are originally Iranian, your ethnicity is typically categorized as **Persian**, which is the dominant ethnic group in Iran. However, Iran is also home to various other ethnic groups, such as Azeris, Kurds, Lurs, Baloch, Arabs, and others. If you identify with one of these groups, you can specify that instead.\n\nOn most application forms, you might see options like:\n\n- **Middle Eastern** or **West Asian** (broader regional category)\n- **Iranian** or **Persian** (specific to your ethnicity)\n- **Other** (if your specific ethnicity is not listed, with an option to write it in)\n\nIf the form does not explicitly list Persian or Iranian, selecting **Middle Eastern**, **West Asian**, or **Other** would be appropriate, depending on the options provided. Always choose the option that best aligns with your self-identification. If in doubt, you can clarify in additional comments or documentation.",
